reviews.title: Perfect 👌🏻
reviews.text: Today we docked for the first time in the harbour in Urk and spontaneously reserved a table at 't Achterhuis. Great location, great views, nice Mood, friendly service. And most importantly, mega delicious food. I ordered the Surf & Turf and it exceeded my expectations. The beef was super tender with tasty roasted aromas, plus the prawns in a really delicious sweet chili sauce. Some of the crew indulged in the Chateaubriand... Everyone was extremely enthusiastic. All in all, we can recommend the restaurant with conviction. All thumbs up 👍🏻

reviews.title: Poor staff
reviews.text: I ate at this restaurant yesterday the food wasn't special I had a threesome fish platter. But the staff sucks We sat down somewhere we were first asked to sit somewhere else and then we weren't done and she wanted to take our plates down and when we were done they want to know immediately if we want dessert to the most hurried staff as if she didn't feel like working and would rather go home

reviews.title: Overpriced and Mediocre Food
reviews.text: My Dutch friends bought me over to Urk on their boat and I insisted I was going to treat them to dinner so they made reservations for this place. There was plenty of room so we sat inside at a table overlooking the boat docking. The menu was in Dutch so I had my friend help me but I think I still didn't totally understand it all. They ordered fish and pork tenderloin and I ordered the very expensive surf and turf steak and gambas. I thought potatoes came with it and I asked if I could have potatoes that were not French fries. My friend got us a bottle of wine for the table and we ordered bottled waters as well. The steak was cooked medium rare as I requested, I should have asked for a steak knife as it was tough to cut with a regular table knife. I am used to having the kitchen slice a thick steak and present it on a board. French fries were put on the table and I remarked that I thought I was to get other potatoes so after a wait, a bowl of fried potato chunks was presented which isn't much different than French fries. Surrounding my steak was some measly mushy unappetizing vegetables and the gambas were in some sort of a sauce which I wish I could have known what it was as I got terribly ill on our walk back to the boat. My friends seemed satisfied with their choices but none of us were impressed with the food. We asked for 2 more waters which we never got. When paying there was a 5 euro charge for these extra potatoes I ordered and I guess I didn't understand when ordering we were getting French fries and these were an extra charge. They were late coming to the table and we really ate very little of them. My dinner was very expensive at 37.50 plus the extra 5 for the potatoes and I was not satisfied with any of it, the steak was not flavourful and hard to cut. I didn't eat much of it.  The gambas sauce made me sick. This was a complete waste of money and we were sorry we came. There is nothing special about this place.

reviews.title: Medium
reviews.text: Not very special. Very limited vegetarian options. The puffed potato was more of a potato cooked in the skin than actually puffed and also not really cooked (very hard). Fish salad was fine, fries nice. Think they are very focused on customers who only come once and therefore do not try very hard.

reviews.title: Nice out in Urk
reviews.text: Just nice restaurant where everything checks out. Good service, good food both fish and meat. Nice table at the window.Come back gladly.

reviews.title: Cozy and tasty
reviews.text: A beautiful location and we had a great meal. Fun, smooth service and you sit at ease! Highly recommended!

reviews.title: Bad
reviews.text:
Expensive and then you get canned tomato soup with canned balls. Bread bad and meagre!
Not recommended waste of your money.
Only positive is the location

reviews.title: Very expensive and no better than a snack bar or lunchroom.
reviews.text:
Cup of hot water with a flavour (tea) € 3.30
Cup of coffee € 3.30
Ham sandwich € 12.50
Ham and cheese bouncer € 12.50
Of course you can view the map and order or not. Own choice. 
No more walking past all the other nice places and then being stripped. Yeah, I know. You do it yourself but it may be a bit less for the quality because it is certainly not special. A snack bar is definitely just as good.
The bill at the bottom says: "Thank you for visiting"
I get that, but we'll never get there again.

reviews.title: Pleasant surprise
reviews.text: All the other restaurants in Urk were closed so we ended up here by chance. Luckily so, the service was friendly and fast. Food very simple but perfectly cooked fresh fish, so tasty. The most amazing views on the terrace. Surely a place to revisit

reviews.title: Lesje hospitality would not be a luxury.
reviews.text:
Bad experience in the Secret Annex. You come in, there are 3 staff at the bar, not one of them welcomed us. Started with three drinks, this immediately went wrong. Expensive dishes, little on your plate. Looking at the menu, an overpriced snack bar rather than a (fish) restaurant on the harbor. 
Conclusion: Worth your money nNIEY.

reviews.title: Very good
reviews.text: Delicious food, good quality, even though we were here yesterday on May 1, 2024, my good friend was still able to order the special King's Day menu, excellent service

reviews.title: good and tasty
reviews.text: We ate sole there. It was very fresh and well prepared and we all enjoyed it. The price/performance ratio is top notch. The wine selection was also very good.

reviews.title: Always good
reviews.text: Really good food and fast service! Nice people and always come here when we are in Urk!! It's always good and fresh!

reviews.title: Good food, but no smoking in the entire restaurant.
reviews.text: Excellent food, both my wife and I had the fish salad. Good and friendly service. It's a pity that smoking is allowed on the partly covered terrace, which is really outdated. I don't understand how a restaurant allows the enjoyment of good food to be ruined for many by a few die-hard smokers who cannot have the decency to smoke outside instead of near people eating. Immediately do not allow anymore. For me a reason to eat elsewhere from now on.

reviews.title: Gang of scammers
reviews.text: You order a Zeetong, you get Sliptong, but you pay for Zeetong. It's unbelievable how easily they try to get away with it. You order a bottle of wine, you get two glasses, because the bottles are supposedly gone, but they try to get you to pay for the bottle. One big scammer gang here in Urk. Never again !

It’s one of the best ways to get a glimpse into a destination's culture, traditions, and history, whether it’s through its local dishes, ingredients, or culinary customs. But if you really want to embrace local culture, there’s no better way than over a glass. reviews.title: Excellent service
reviews.text: We arrived at this restaurant by chance. Although the hour was late and they were already cleaning the kitchen, they allowed us to dine. Really nice and friendly staff and an excellent dinner.

reviews.title: Good location for a quick coffee and more
reviews.text: We ended up at this place only to get a coffee (and to use the loo, which I must be honest is a very good service provided by the restaurant to the community and visitors, since you do not need to enter the main place to make use of it) and we sort of had almost the full deal. Service was fast, polite and efficient. The view to the sea bank outstanding. It’s definitely worth coming and enjoy the place with a bit more calm than we did

reviews.title: Great location, but a bit pricey
reviews.text: We stopped here for a late lunch.  The fish was good, but not very big.  The salads and chips were good, but if you want bread there is an extra cost.  The food took a long time to come.  The big attraction is the location, but we found the food to be nothing special and the price to go along with the location.  I would return but I would try somewhere else first.

reviews.title: Great views
reviews.text: We stopped for a refreshment when we arrived at the harbour. Spectacular views from the upstairs terrace and great service.

reviews.title: Excellent food and service!
reviews.text:
Just a gem in the polder, excellent food and service! Service was friendly and polite, food was excellent and tasty, first course we had a sample of smoked fish and schrimp cocktail, portions were big and tasty and served with fresh baked bread and butter.
Main course we had a selection of plaice, soo good..and plenty and dessert was made as surprise from chef and he came to our table! Excellent! But first of all good service and food and view of the sea.

reviews.title: Nice view and high service
reviews.text:
Went there for a buisness lunch. 
The menu covers a wide range of dishes, and a mix of meet and fish. 
The view over the marina is nice and relaxing.

reviews.title: Great Spot for Fish and Views
reviews.text:
I never expected this place in Urk. It reminded me of California: on the top floor with panorama views of the harbor. Had a late lunch and the service was quick and friendly. The kabeljauw was crisp and delicious, exactly what I wanted. 

We will absolutely be back as I expect this will be an amazing spot to watch a sunset.

reviews.title: Worst experience ever
reviews.text: We waited more than an hour for our food, then followed up with the waiter only to find out that our food order wasn't placed.  When the food eventually arrived, it wasn't even what we ordered.  Really bad experience.

reviews.title: Nice view, not so great service
reviews.text:
The view was indeed wonderful, but the service poor. We were with a party of five which included four adults and one child.  First of all we had to wait an hour for our food to come. We had ordered pretty soon after we arrived and after we got our drinks had to wait an hour for our main course. The soup which belonged to a menu did come quick, but only two of us ordered a menu so the rest of us was waiting. In the mean time we were asked if we wanted more to drink by at least two different people. This is nice, but it would have been better if the two different servers would talk to eachother so they would know that this question had already been asked, 
Eventually our food came. We had ordered two senior meals, because the portions would be smaller. It turned out that the portions were not smaller but still pretty big. Anyway, the food we got was good and tasty. However we had to share three small bowls of fries, potatoes and vegetables which was not enough for the five of us. We had to order more to satisfy us all. We had ordered this fairly soon after we got our food, but it came after we had almost eaten all of our food which was not really how we had meant it to be. 
We also did not get napkins, but the server brought us more later.

Also, in the end we did not get a bill by our table. We were asked to go to the counter to pay. We ended up staying in line with other people. It seemed like a supermarket where you had a to pay your groceries.

I think for a restaurant with these kind of prices (most meals are on average 21 euros) the service can be better, the portions, and it would be nice to just have a bill served by the table instead of having to stand in line.

reviews.title: Lecture
reviews.text:
Visited this restaurant for a lecture of a Photographer.
Coffee and tea were part of the arrangement.
Special for our youngest the owner made a nice chocolate drink.
Beautiful views over the harbour and the IJselmeer. Friendly staff. We will be back for lunch or dinner

reviews.title: Great fish
reviews.text:
This used to be a large fishing port and this restaurant was a shack that cooked whatever fish was landed.

It has now become a good quality restaurant specialising in fresh fish.

The restaurant looks out over the harbour and has lovely views.

We ordered the set menu and were served with a plentiful supply of lovely fish.  

The starter was fish soup which was also excellent and the desserts were massive.

Staff were very friendly.

reviews.title: very friendly staff excellent food
reviews.text: This restaurant is in a excellent location. It is overlooking the water with a large patio eating area with great views. We all had fish, filet of sole and another local fish, All meals were well presented and tasted amazing. When the owner found out, from the waiter, that we were Canadians he came over and talked to us for a long while.

reviews.title: Nice View , Bad Kitchen
reviews.text:
We had not been to URK for many years and decided to revisit URK and enjoy a good fish dinner which should be easy considering that URK is a fishing town.
We decided to eat at 't Achterhuis which is located in the harbour overlooking the Ijsselmeer. the waitress was friendly but she too good not compensate for the terrible meal we were served.
My wife went for the place and I ordered dover sole both to be prepared naturel no herbs. Both the Place and Sole were not prepared as ordered , the Sole was completely dry and filled with roe which is nice if you like it but terrible if you don't like it. The side dishes were a joke friend potatoes too well done some hourse before serving , cauliflower and french endive not good.

reviews.title: Great gourmet platter
reviews.text:
My sis and I shared the gourmet platter (for two) and also ordered a fish soup. Every morsel of fish, beef, pâte, shrimp, eel, etc. was exquisite. No regrets ordering that. The fish soup was more like tomato soup with fish pieces in it. Perhaps the cook can try create something different with this? 

My brother-in-law ordered a hamburger and said it was delicious. View from the external deck seatings are wonderful as you see the fishing village of Urk and boats coming and going. Altogether a lovely place for lunch and I am sure the ambience would be great at night as well.

reviews.title: The best in URK!
reviews.text:
I've been there twice. One with clients who living in URK and they took me and one with my wife.
Great food, fresh seafood and Beautyfull view!
Don't miss this place!
